== Roasted Carrots and Onion ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Trim, peel, and halve @carrots{6%ounce} lengthwise; slice into 1⁄2-inch-thick
half moons. Halve, peel, and cut @red onion{1%unit} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges.

Toss carrots and onion on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{},
@cumin{1%teaspoon}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Roast on
the top rack until tender, ~{18-20%minutes}.

== Garlic Couscous ==

While veggies roast, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #small pot{} over
medium-high heat. Add @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce} and @garlic powder{1%teaspoon};
cook, stirring frequently, until garlic powder is fragrant and couscous is
lightly toasted, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @water{3/4%cup} and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover
and reduce heat to low. Cook until couscous is tender, ~{6-8%minutes}. Keep
covered until ready to serve.

== Marinated Tomatoes ==

While couscous cooks, halve @grape tomatoes{4%ounce} and roughly chop
@pistachios{1/2%ounce}.

In a #large bowl{}, whisk @red wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, @olive oil{2%TBSP},
@salt{1%tsp}, and @sugar{1/2%tsp} until sugar is dissolved. Add tomatoes and
toss until thoroughly coated.

> Save remaining vinegar, olive oil, salt, and sugar for 4 servings: use 10 tsp
> vinegar, 4 TBSP olive oil, 2 tsp salt, and 1 tsp sugar total.

== Salmon ==

Pat @salmon{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add salmon (skin sides down). Cook salmon until skin is crisp and fish
is almost cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes}, then flip and cook until cooked
through, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}.

> Pat chicken or salmon dry with paper towels to achieve a good sear.

== Assembly ==

Once veggies are roasted and couscous is cooked, stir into bowl with
marinated tomatoes; add @spinach{5%ounce} and toss until spinach is slightly
wilted.

Divide spinach salad between bowls and top with @feta cheese{1/2%cup}(crumbled)
and pistachios. Serve.

Slice chicken crosswise (skip slicing salmon!). Top salad with chicken or salmon
and garnish with feta and pistachios.

> Fish is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.